<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="126" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1269,2017]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1269,1294]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Scutum entirely black. Fore coxa yellow, mid and hind coxae brown; femora yellow except for distal 
<number box="[1414,1425,1270,1294]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[151,165,1305,1330]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="6.0">6</number>
of fore femur, distal 
<number box="[401,411,1306,1330]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[421,437,1306,1330]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="4.0">4</number>
of mid femur and distal 
<number box="[714,724,1306,1330]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[735,749,1306,1330]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="3.0">3</number>
of hind femur brown; tibiae and tarsi brown except for tibiae yellow basally. R 
<number box="[350,358,1356,1370]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[367,374,1356,1370]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[460,466,1356,1370]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[476,485,1356,1370]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="2.0">2</number>
convergent distally. Cercus incised on ventral margin, the depth 
<number box="[1243,1253,1342,1366]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1264,1278,1342,1366]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="3.0">3</number>
of its height. Postgonite with a long process on inner distal end.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1269,2017]" box="[199,998,1416,1441]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1416,1441]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">Description</emphasis>
. Male. Body length 
<quantity box="[567,704,1416,1440]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="2.45" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.2">2.2–2.7 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[856,994,1416,1440]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="2.2" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="2.1">2.1–2.3 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1269,2017]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">
Head yellow with gray microtomentum, 
<number box="[664,699,1453,1477]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="0.9">0.9</number>
times as long as high; face yellow, somewhat concave in lateral view, without facial carina; frons black except for anterior 
<number box="[824,834,1488,1512]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[844,860,1488,1512]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="4.0">4</number>
yellow, 
<number box="[958,993,1488,1512]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="0.9">0.9</number>
times as long as wide, projecting only slightly in front of eye; gena yellow with ventral margin black, broad, 
<number box="[982,1017,1524,1549]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="0.5">0.5</number>
times as wide as first flagellomere; parafacial indistinct. Ocellar triangle black, reaching anterior 
<number box="[862,874,1560,1584]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[883,897,1560,1584]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="4.0">4</number>
of frons, with a pointed anterior apex; ocellar tubercle light brown. Occiput and postgena black. Clypeus light brown. Cephalic setae and setulae black. Antenna yellow with thick grayish microtomentum except for dorsal 
<number box="[833,843,1632,1656]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[853,869,1632,1656]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="2.0">2</number>
of first flagellomere brown; first flagellomere 
<number box="[1401,1436,1632,1656]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="0.8">0.8</number>
times as long as wide; arista brown with short brown setulae. Proboscis bright brown to yellow with brown setulae; palpus yellow with black setulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1269,2017]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,255]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">
Thorax black with gray microtomentum. Scutum as long as wide. Thoracic pleuron shiny brown without microtomentum except for posteroventral portion of propleuron, anteroventral portion of anepisternum, anterior portion of katepisternum bright black. Scutellum 
<number box="[711,746,1813,1837]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="0.7">0.7</number>
times as long as wide; 
<emphasis box="[1013,1073,1813,1836]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">ap sc</emphasis>
developed, 
<number box="[1211,1246,1813,1837]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.7">1.7</number>
times as long as scutellum; 
<emphasis box="[277,349,1849,1872]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">sap sc</emphasis>
<number box="[360,395,1848,1872]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.2">1.2</number>
times as long as scutellum. Setae and setulae on thorax black, developed; 
<emphasis box="[1269,1305,1848,1872]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">npl</emphasis>
<number box="[1315,1327,1848,1872]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1348,1360,1848,1872]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.0">1</number>
, 
<emphasis box="[1376,1436,1848,1872]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">a npl</emphasis>
developed, 
<emphasis box="[279,336,1884,1908]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">p npl</emphasis>
hair-like, subequal to 
<emphasis box="[585,642,1884,1908]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">a npl</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis box="[656,705,1885,1908]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">a pa</emphasis>
developed; 
<emphasis box="[841,889,1885,1908]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">p pa</emphasis>
hair-like, subequal to 
<emphasis box="[1139,1188,1885,1908]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">a pa</emphasis>
; 
<number box="[1202,1216,1885,1909]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.0">1</number>
presutural 
<emphasis box="[1341,1367,1884,1908]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">dc</emphasis>
and 
<number box="[1422,1436,1885,1909]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="3.0">3</number>
postsutural 
<emphasis box="[282,308,1920,1944]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="126">dc</emphasis>
, the posterior one longer than others. Fore coxa yellow, mid and hind coxae brown; femora yellow except for distal 
<number box="[347,357,1956,1981]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[367,382,1956,1981]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="6.0">6</number>
of fore femur, distal 
<number box="[633,643,1957,1981]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[653,669,1957,1981]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="4.0">4</number>
of mid femur and distal 
<number box="[962,972,1957,1981]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[983,997,1957,1981]" pageId="4" pageNumber="126" value="3.0">3</number>
of hind femur brown; tibiae and tarsi brown except for tibiae yellow basally. Setulae on legs black. Mid and hind tibiae each with a short black apical spur, which are shorter than diameter of tibia. Tibial organ oblong, narrow. Wing 
<number box="[1054,1089,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as long as wide, hyaline; veins brown. Relative lengths of 
<number box="[527,540,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="2.0">2</number>
nd: 
<number box="[592,604,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="3.0">3</number>
rd: 
<number box="[654,668,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="4.0">4</number>
th costal sections = 
<number box="[893,907,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="4.0">4</number>
: 
<number box="[931,945,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="3.0">3</number>
: 
<number box="[969,984,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="1.0">1</number>
; r-m at basal 
<number box="[1141,1176,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="0.5">0.5</number>
of discal cell; R 
<number box="[1363,1371,203,217]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1380,1387,203,217]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[176,181,241,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[191,200,241,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="2.0">2</number>
convergent distally. Halter pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231680/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" targetBox="[316,1267,311,1286]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1435,1314,1367]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127">
