</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1406,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127">
Abdomen brown with gray microtomentum except for sides of tergite 
<number box="[1033,1047,1407,1431]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="1.0">1</number>
black; venter yellow. Setulae on abdomen black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1406,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[381,506,1478,1503]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1314,1337]" captionTargetBox="[316,1267,311,1286]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[309,1277,306,1292]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 11. Apotropina longiprocessa sp. n., male. 8 male terminalia, posterior view; 9 male terminalia, lateral view; 10 hypandrium and phallic complex, ventral view; 11 hypandrium and phallic complex, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231680/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="127">
Figs. 
<number box="[446,506,1479,1503]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="9.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="8.0">8–11</number>
</figureCitation>
): Epandrium brown with ventrodistal corner narrowly prolonged; surstylus acute apically. Cercus weakly convex on dorsal margin, incised on ventral margin, the depth 
<number box="[1127,1137,1515,1539]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1148,1162,1515,1539]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="3.0">3</number>
of its height. Postgonite and pregonite subequal in length, postgonite with a long process on inner distal end; distiphallus longer than basiphallus in lateral view; phallapodeme long with basal stalk broad in lateral view. Hypandrium narrowed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1406,2011]" box="[199,871,1622,1647]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127">
Female. Body length 
<quantity box="[440,577,1623,1647]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3499999999999996" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" unit="mm" value="3.3499999999999996" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="2.8">2.8–3.9 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[729,867,1622,1647]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" unit="mm" value="2.85" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="2.6">2.6–3.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1406,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[403,543,1658,1683]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1074,1097]" captionTargetBox="[322,1263,350,1047]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[316,1270,342,1052]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 14. Apotropina longiprocessa sp. n. female. 12 abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; 13 abdominal terminalia, lateral view; 14 abdominal terminalia, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231681/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="127">
Figs. 
<number box="[468,543,1659,1683]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="13.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="12.0">12–14</number>
</figureCitation>
): epiproct pentagonal, distinctly wider than long, with 
<number box="[1169,1183,1659,1683]" pageId="5" pageNumber="127" value="4.0">4</number>
long setae; hypoproct long, apically round with long stout setae. Cercus short and stout with some long setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
